cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.DS, cs.NI 

This paper belongs to the computer science sub-category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) as it analyzes the online tracking ecosystem and its impact on user privacy. Additionally, it may also fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI) as it constructs graphs to analyze the relationships between trackers and publishers. The paper also involves data analysis and statistics (cs.CY) to measure changes in tracking activity over time. Furthermore, it may fall under the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) as it involves constructing graphs and analyzing network activity.
